Notes: The 'row_id' likely corresponds to a record identifier; using 'hasRecordDateTime' is a placeholder. However, since none of the paths directly indicate an ID, this is an approximation. Alternatively, a dedicated identifier property would be ideal if available.
Patient identifiers are best linked through 'hasSubjectPseudoIdentifier', which connects the problem condition to the patient pseudonym, reflecting patient identity.
Diagnosis codes are best mapped through 'hasCode', directly linking the problem condition to its coding concept.
Timestamp data naturally maps to 'hasDateTime', capturing the creation or relevant date of the record.
Organizational code can be associated with the data provider institute, indicating the source or managing organization.
Organization name complements the organization code, providing descriptive detail linked via 'hasDataProviderInstitute'.
